[1.504519, "o", "===============================================\r\n       hermes-router — installation demo\r\n===============================================\r\n\r\n"]
[2.505765, "o", "STEP 1/8  Install (one command, no cd needed)\r\n\r\n"]
[3.506846, "o", "  $ python3 -c \"$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/\r\n      jphermans/hermes-router-cli/main/bootstrap-install.py)\"\r\n"]
[4.508044, "o", "\r\n  (... downloads, extracts, runs install.py, sets up plugin ...)\r\n"]
[5.509057, "o", "\r\n  Result:\r\n    ✓ .venv created\r\n    ✓ PyYAML installed\r\n"]
[5.509216, "o", "    ✓ hr symlink at ~/.local/bin/hr\r\n    ✓ Plugin written to ~/.hermes/plugins/hermes-router/\r\n"]
[7.510161, "o", "\r\nSTEP 2/8  Verify the install\r\n\r\n"]
[8.51119, "o", "  $ hr --version\r\n"]
[8.630737, "o", "hermes-router 1.0.0\r\n"]
[10.659204, "o", "\r\n\r\nSTEP 3/8  Health check (basic)\r\n\r\n"]
[11.660231, "o", "  $ hr doctor\r\n"]
[11.797114, "o", "✓ config.yaml                loaded 11 providers\r\n✓ providers with keys        10/11 have at least one key configured\r\n✓ cost-class coverage        free: 5 providers, paid: 5 providers\r\n✓ free pool usable           21 free model(s) available\r\n✓ paid pool usable           16 paid model(s) available\r\n✓ all providers have base_url  all set\r\n"]
[13.825298, "o", "\r\n\r\nSTEP 4/8  Health check (verbose — per-provider details)\r\n"]
[13.825444, "o", "\r\n"]
[14.826601, "o", "  $ hr doctor --verbose\r\n"]
[14.971269, "o", "✓ config.yaml                loaded 11 providers\r\n✓ providers with keys        10/11 have at least one key configured\r\n✓ cost-class coverage        free: 5 providers, paid: 5 providers\r\n✓ free pool usable           21 free model(s) available\r\n✓ paid pool usable           16 paid model(s) available\r\n✓ all providers have base_url  all set\r\n✓ provider details:\r\n"]
[14.971395, "o", "     zai                free  🔑 1 key(s)  https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4\r\n                               models: glm-4.5-air, glm-4.5, glm-4.5v, glm-4.6 … (9 total)\r\n     kilo               free  🔑 1 key(s)  https://api.kilo.ai/api/gateway\r\n                               models: tencent/hy3, deepseek-v4-pro\r\n     minimax            free  🔑 1 key(s)  https://api.minimax.io/v1\r\n                               models: MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed, MiniMax-M2.7, MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed, MiniMax-M3\r\n     github_models      free  🔑 1 key(s)  https://models.inference.ai.azure.com\r\n                               models: gpt-4o-mini, gpt-4o, phi-3.5-mini-instruct\r\n     gemini             free  ❌ 0 key(s)  https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/openai\r\n                               models: gemini-2.5-flash, gemini-2.5-flash-lite, gemini-2.0-flash\r\n     openrouter_free    free  🔑 1 key(s)  https://openrouter.ai/api/v1\r\n                               models: meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free, google/gemini-2.0-flash-exp:free, qwen/qwen-2.5-72b-instruct:free\r\n     deepseek           paid  🔑 1 key(s)  https://api.deepseek.com\r\n                               models: deepseek-chat, deepseek-reasoner\r\n     openrouter         paid  🔑 1 key(s)  https://openrouter.ai/api/v1\r\n                               models: deepseek/deepseek-chat-v3-0324, google/gemini-2.0-flash-001, meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct, anthropic/claude-3.5-sonnet … (5 total)\r\n     xai                paid  🔑 1 key(s)  https://api.x.ai/v1\r\n                               models: grok-2-mini, grok-2\r\n     nvidia             paid  🔑 1 key(s)  https://integrate.api.nvidia.com/v1\r\n                               models: meta/llama-3.1-8b-instruct, meta/llama-3.1-70b-instruct\r\n     venice             paid  🔑 1 key(s)  https://api.venice.ai/api/v1\r\n                               models: openai-gpt-oss-120b, mistral-small-3-2-24b-instruct, deepseek-v4-flash, qwen3-235b-a22b-instruct-2507 … (5 total)\r\n"]
[17.999015, "o", "\r\n\r\nSTEP 5/8  Route a prompt — cheapest free model wins\r\n\r\n"]
[19.000083, "o", "  $ hr route --prompt \"Say hello in Dutch\" --class free --pretty\r\n"]
[23.013488, "o", "✓ github_models/gpt-4o-mini  (~$0.000000, 1 tries)\r\n\r\nHello in Dutch is \"Hallo.\"\r\n"]
[25.044943, "o", "\r\n\r\n"]
[25.04511, "o", "STEP 6/8  Auto-fallback — try free first, fall back to paid if needed\r\n\r\n"]
[26.046254, "o", "  $ hr route --prompt \"Why is the sky blue?\" --class free --auto-fallback --pretty\r\n"]
[39.203804, "o", "✓ github_models/gpt-4o-mini  (~$0.000000, 1 tries)\r\n\r\nThe sky appears blue primarily due to a phenomenon called Rayleigh scattering. When sunlight enters the Earth's atmosphere, it is made up of various colors, which correspond to different wavelengths. Blue light has a shorter wavelength compared to other colors like red or yellow.\r\n\r\nAs sunlight passes through the atmosphere, it interacts with air molecules and small particles. The shorter blue wavelengths are scattered in all directions more effectively than the longer wavelengths. This scattering process causes more blue light to be visible from all angles, giving the sky its characteristic blue color during the day.\r\n\r\nDuring sunrise and sunset, the sky can appear red or orange because the sunlight passes through a greater thickness of the atmosphere, scattering the shorter blue wavelengths out of the direct path of sight and allowing the longer red wavelengths to become more prominent.\r\n"]
[41.233165, "o", "\r\n\r\nSTEP 7/8  Track your spending\r\n\r\n"]
[42.234204, "o", "  $ hr budget --last 3\r\n"]
[42.35032, "o", "── 2026-07 ──\r\n  github_models         $    0.0000\r\n  TOTAL                 $    0.0000\r\n\r\n"]
[44.378264, "o", "\r\n\r\nSTEP 8/8  Enable the Hermes plugin so you can use it from chat\r\n\r\n"]
[45.379289, "o", "  $ hermes plugins enable hermes-router --allow-tool-override\r\n"]
[45.798532, "o", "Plugin 'hermes-router' is already enabled.\r\n"]
[45.82567, "o", "✓ Granted hermes-router permission to override built-in tools \r\n(plugins.entries.hermes-router.allow_tool_override: true).\r\n"]
[47.409786, "o", "\r\n\r\n===============================================\r\n       Now use it from any Hermes session\r\n"]
[47.409913, "o", "===============================================\r\n\r\n  After /reset, just say in plain language:\r\n\r\n    > Run hr_doctor to check my providers\r\n"]
[47.410214, "o", "    > Route this through the free pool: vertaal hallo naar Frans\r\n    > Show me hr_models with only free providers\r\n\r\n"]
[49.41104, "o", "  Works in CLI, Telegram, Discord, Slack — anywhere Hermes runs.\r\n\r\n"]
